---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="The Library's Argument · Reading Room · America's School Trust Library"
  description="Two paired works — Sacred Compact (the analytic frame) and Schools of the Republic (the case-by-case record) — that together carry the Library's argument."
  sourceId="reading-librarys-argument"
>
  <article class="prose prose-slate max-w-none prose-a:text-blue-700 prose-a:underline">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">Reading Room · Section I</p>
    <h1 class="mt-2">The Library's Argument</h1>
    <p class="kicker text-slate-600">
      Two volumes. One argument. The analytic frame and the case-by-case record.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Library's Argument runs across two paired works. <a href="/reading/sacred-compact/"><em>Sacred Compact</em></a> is
      the analytic frame: what the school-trust experiment was, what happened to it
      across two and a half centuries, and what it teaches the architects of the
      AI-era trusts now arriving. <a href="/reading/schools-of-the-republic/"><em>Schools of the Republic</em></a> is the empirical
      floor — fifty states, two hundred and forty years, named principals and named
      cases, the evidence that warrants the diagnosis. The two volumes are designed
      to be read either way: the frame first if you want the argument, the record
      first if you want the proof. They converge on a single conclusion —
      institutions holding multi-generational fiduciary inheritances drift in
      characteristic ways, and the country has now run the experiment long enough
      that the lessons can be transferred to the trusts being designed today.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
      <a href="/contribute/">Suggest a contribution</a> — corrections, source
      material, and citizen-historian work are welcome.
    </p>
  </article>

  <section class="argument-cards mt-12">
    <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <li class="argument-card">
        <p class="card-kicker">Volume I · The analytic frame</p>
        <h2 class="card-title">
          <em>Sacred Compact</em>: A Forever Gift to Forever Schools for a Forever Democracy
        </h2>
        <p class="card-byline">Dave Sullivan with Margaret Bird</p>
        <p class="card-length">~70 pages — eight essays plus three personal interludes</p>
        <p class="card-blurb">
          The analytic argument. Eight essays trace the school-trust experiment from
          the 1785 Land Ordinance through the AI-era forever-trusts now being
          designed. Three personal interludes — Tektronix, Computing Today, cognitive
          partnership — ground the argument in lived experience of institutional
          drift.
        </p>
        <a href="/reading/sacred-compact-prologue/" class="card-cta">Begin reading →</a>
      </li>

      <li class="argument-card">
        <p class="card-kicker">Volume II · The empirical record</p>
        <h2 class="card-title">
          <em>Schools of the Republic</em>: A Case-by-Case Record of America's School Trust Lands
        </h2>
        <p class="card-byline">Margaret Bird with Dave Sullivan</p>
        <p class="card-length">
          ~494 pages — Part I (nine chapters of synthesis) plus Part II (per-state
          evidentiary entries integrated into the Atlas)
        </p>
        <p class="card-blurb">
          The evidentiary floor. Nine chapters synthesize the founding floor, the
          antebellum doubling, the Reconstruction western stack, the
          twentieth-century high-water mark, and the captured-AG architecture that
          emerged in the late twentieth century. Reform-attempt thread runs alongside
          the drift narrative throughout.
        </p>
        <a href="/reading/prologue/" class="card-cta">Begin reading →</a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <p class="mt-12 text-sm text-slate-600">
    <a href="/reading/">← Back to the Reading Room</a>
  </p>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .argument-cards ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .argument-card {
    background: var(--linen-card, #fafaf7);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-border, #e5e7eb);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--old-gold, #8b7355);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.5rem 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, box-shadow 0.15s ease;
  }
  .argument-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.06);
  }
  .card-kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--old-gold, #8b7355);
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .card-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif, Georgia, serif);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--deep-navy, #1e3a5f);
    line-height: 1.35;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .card-byline {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #475569;
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .card-length {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #64748b;
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
  }
  .card-blurb {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: #334155;
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
    flex: 1;
  }
  .card-cta {
    align-self: flex-start;
    color: #1d4ed8;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .card-cta:hover {
    color: #1e40af;
  }
</style>
